  "extras": {
    "summary": "AN ACT TO REQUIRE AN EMPLOYER TO PROVIDE A WRITTEN EARNINGS STATEMENT TO AN EMPLOYEE UPON RECEIVING A WRITTEN REQUEST; TO SPECIFY THE INFORMATION THAT MUST BE INCLUDED IN THE WRITTEN EARNINGS STATEMENT; TO REQUIRE THE OFFICE OF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL TO PROVIDE INFORMATION ON ITS WEBSITE REGARDING AN EMPLOYEE'S RIGHT TO REQUEST A WRITTEN EARNINGS STATEMENT AND TO FILE A COMPLAINT AGAINST AN EMPLOYER WHO FAILS TO PROVIDE SUCH STATEMENT; TO IMPOSE A $750.00 FINE ON ANY EMPLOYER WHO VIOLATES THIS ACT; AND FOR RELATED PURPOSES."
  },
